svg.title: editorial
svg.text: Sometimes things in life don’t go as planned. When I was eight years old, I remember sitting at the creek with my sisters. We had a ton of experience being around water — or so we thought. The water was calm and inviting. Liz, my older sister, dared me to jump in. “No way,” I yelled. Sara, the younger dashed away into the water. “Ouch!” she cried. Her head dipped below the surface and so did my stomach.
